## Feature summary

+ Visitors can register/log in
+ Gereral Users can add/delete appointments with specified veterinarian, the schedules that are not available is hidden automatically
+ General Users can also view the news from the clinic on the home page slide show
+ Admin Users can add/update/delete veterinarian information the administrator account
+ Admin Users can add/update/delete News slide with the administrator account
+ Account registered with first name "rootuser" are admin accounts, They can access the admin features
+ The navigation menu is changed according to the account type


## Database summary
*Describe the tables and relationships used in your database. Delete the examples below and replace with your own info.*

+ My application has 4 tables in total (`users`, `appointments`, `veterinarians`, `slides`)
+ There's a many-to-many relationship between `appointments` and `veterinarians`
+ There's a one-to-many relationship between `appointments` and `users`

